negotiator.gui.progress

Enum DataKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DataKey>
      • negotiator.gui.progress.DataKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DataKey>

    public enum DataKey
extends java.lang.Enum<DataKey>
implements java.lang.Comparable<DataKey>
    These keys are datatypes for data , eg in HashMaps. See e.g. AgreementEvent.getValues(). The keys also have a human-readable text version. This can be used as basis for the column text strings for data display and logging. The keys UTILS, FILES and AGENTS contain lists. The function AgreementEvent#getFlatMap() and AgreementEvent.getValues() will convert these to strings and extend these keys with the agent number, and we then have eg 3 columns "Utility 1", "Utility 2" and "Utility 3" in the table. In the map, the UTILS field will be an List with 3 values in that case. see also AgreementEvent#getKeys(). The DataKeyTableModel can handle such data directly. Note that the order of the enum is irrelevant; the order in which the keys are provided to the DataKeyTableModel determines the column order.
    Author:
    W.Pasman 16jul15
